                      <span>2005-03-21</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I just passed my PMP, but I cannot say it was due to this book. I bought this book and then a colleague let me use his Andy Crowe book...and this is the one that I will praise.
<br />
<br />Rita's book is too heavy on useless exercises, and as some people pointed out, she makes you feel stupid. Her questions are too convoluted and are not close to the actual exam questions. The actual exam was more like the final exam in Crowe's book.
<br />
<br />Although, I have to say that some questions I would not have been able to answer if it was not for this book, but it was a good complementary study for me.
<br />
<br />If you are choosing between this one and Andy's book - buy Crowe's, not Rita's.
<br />
<br /></span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A must have!</div>
